==> TOPIC: BACK IN THE SADDLE

Greetings:

Did ya miss me over the Christmas, er, holiday (politically correct)
break?  I know I missed you.  And it's fairly obvious that no amount
of stale fruitcakes could keep the world's branding issues from
burning into I-Branders' minds.  Personally, I spent the time off
moving my FrankelBiz Branded Community to its new i-legions
platform. It's still in its infancy, with more services being
finalized over this month, but you can feast your baby blues on it
at http://www.Frankelbiz.com if you like.

In the meantime, there are plenty of soul-searching issues to tickle
your fancy this week, not the least of which is a new I-Brander's
sincere request for help in telling the real branding stuff from the
fakes.

I also am pleased to report that every indication I see points to an
increase in branding activity, both as a discipline and a required
marketing tool.  I believe that 2003 is the year that will see
branding gain its own respectability, formally differentiated from
advertising, marketing and other related fields.

Which is good, considering this is how I make my living....

Lots of stuff to get to.  Let's hear your responses next week!

Your Branding Buddy,

Rob "I answer your questions, but not here" Frankel
http://www.FrankelTips.com -- where Rob answers your questions


